A '''sentientologist''' (also referred to as a '''sapientologist'''<ref name="GG4, 2nd">[[Galaxy Guide 4: Alien Races (Second Edition)|''Galaxy Guide 4: Alien Races'', Second Edition]]</ref> or an '''anthropologist'''<ref name="EGAS">[[The Essential Guide to Alien Species (real-world book)|''The Essential Guide to Alien Species'']]</ref>) was a scientist who studied the biology, culture, and history of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy's]] wide variety of [[Sentience/Legends|sentient]] races and [[Species/Legends|species]].<ref name="GG4">''[[Galaxy Guide 4: Alien Races]]''</ref> The [[University of Sanbra]]'s Sentient Studies Department was one of the main centers for the study of sentientology.<ref name="GG12">''[[Galaxy Guide 12: Aliens — Enemies and Allies]]''</ref> Scholars at the [[University of Coruscant/Legends|University of Coruscant]] were also influential in the field. Under the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], a multi-species committee of scholars at the University of [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] was responsible for classifying species as sentient, semi-sentient, or non-sentient.<ref name="EGAS" />

Prominent sentientologists of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] era included:
*[[Obo Rin]], an Imperial functionary who wrote two editions of ''[[Catalog of Intelligent Life in the Galaxy]]'' under [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader's]] sponsorship<ref name="GG4" />
*[[Ditwar Logas]], a renowned scholar whom Obo Rin claimed to have worked with (though these claims were suspect)<ref name="GG4, 1st">''[[Galaxy Guide 4: Alien Races]]'', First Edition</ref>
*[[Tem Eliss]], an [[Iyra]] professor at the University of [[Sanbra]] who wrote ''[[The University of Sanbra Guide to Intelligent Life]]''<ref name="GG12" />
*Senior Anthropologist [[Mammon Hoole]], an independent [[Shi'ido]] researcher who was the major contributor to ''[[The Essential Guide to Alien Species]]''<ref name="EGAS" />

